    <p class="text-pelorous-500 text-2xl"><strong>PRIVACY POLICY AND PERSONAL DATA (GDPR)</strong></p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500 text-2xl">&nbsp;</p>
    <p>The administrator of your personal data is "ALPHA VISION INVEST" EOOD, ID number 207180738, BULGARIA, city of Plovdiv, post code 4023, Trakia district, g.k. Trakia , entrance A, fl. 5, VAT BG207180738</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>This document contains information regarding the way personal data is processed, the type of personal data that is collected, the purpose of using the collected personal data, the basis for processing, the access of third parties to this data, the security measures that are taken in relation to of the collected personal data, as well as the options available to you in connection with the use of the personal data provided by you.</p>
    <p>All personal data are collected and processed in accordance with the legislation in force in Bulgaria in the field of personal data protection.</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500 mt-3"><strong>1. What personal data do we process?</strong></p>
    <p>When ordering products in the online store: name, email, contact phone number, delivery address. This address, along with your name and contact phone number, is passed on to the courier company we have contracted with to deliver the order. We process the specified personal data that is necessary to be able to perform the service you have requested from us, namely &ndash; delivery of product/s from the online store.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500"><strong>2. Transfer of personal data to third parties:</strong></p>
    <p>We do not provide personal data to third parties, except in expressly listed cases!</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>We may provide access to some personal data for the purposes of storing or organizing our work, or for financial accounting purposes, to processors of personal data with whom we have concluded contracts and have provided for express clauses on the inviolability of personal data, to which the processor can obtain access in the course of your work. In most cases, the information that processors have access to is not enough for them to identify you.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>In order to receive a product that you have ordered through our store, we transmit your name, contact phone number and delivery address, together with the ordered product, to a courier company with which we have a pre-contract. They have their own privacy policy.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500"><strong>3. Security procedures for security</strong></p>
    <p>In accordance with applicable personal data protection laws, we follow mandatory procedures to prevent unauthorized access to and improper use of personal data.</p>
    <p>We use appropriate business systems and procedures to protect and ensure the safety of the personal data you provide to us. We also use security procedures and technical and physical restrictions on the access and use of personal data on our servers. Only authorized personnel have access to personal data for the purposes of their work related to providing a service to the respective client/user.</p>
    <p>We store your personal information as long as it is necessary to guarantee the receipt of the service and as required by the current Bulgarian legislation.</p>
    <p>For financial &amp; accounting purposes, the storage period is 10 years.</p>
    <p>The data we process on the basis of your consent, if there is no other basis for the processing, we destroy immediately after you have withdrawn your consent.</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500">&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500"><strong>4. Your rights in relation to your personal data</strong></p>
    <p>You have rights under applicable law in relation to the data we process, namely:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <p>1. You have the right to request access to and receive information regarding the personal data that is stored about you, as well as information regarding the purposes of processing, the categories of personal data, the recipients to whom your personal data may be disclosed and more;</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>2. You have the right at any time to request the correction of inaccurate data relating to you, as well as the completion of incomplete data, if this is appropriate and/or necessary in view of the purpose for which the data is processed;</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>3. At any time, you can withdraw your consent to the use of your personal data that you previously provided to us, if your consent is the only basis for their processing. In some cases, withdrawing consent to the use or processing of your personal data may result in the inability to benefit from certain products or services provided by us;</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>4. If you decide that you do not want us to process your personal data, you have the right at any time to request that your personal data be deleted if:</p>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="ml-5 text-xs italic">4.1. your personal data are no longer necessary for the purposes for which they were collected or otherwise processed;</p>
    <p class="ml-5 text-xs italic">4.2. in case you have withdrawn your consent to the processing of your personal data and the consent is the only basis for their processing;</p>
    <p class="ml-5 text-xs italic">4.3. if your personal data is processed illegally;</p>
    <p class="ml-5 text-xs italic">4.4. in case you have objected to the processing of your personal data;</p>
    <p class="ml-5 text-xs italic">4.5. other cases provided for in legal acts governing the protection of personal data;</p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <p>5. In a number of cases, you have the right to request, instead of deleting your data, restriction of its processing;</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>6. You also have the right to object by sending an e-mail to www.fairykids.bg against the processing of your personal data;</p>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>If you fear that your personal data is being processed unlawfully, you can contact the national supervisory authority for data protection, which for the Republic of Bulgaria is: Commission for the Protection of Personal Data, Sofia, "Prof. Tsvetan Lazarov" No. 2, with e-mail address: kzld@cpdp.bg and Internet page: www.cpdp.bg;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>You have all the listed rights and can submit a written application in free form by e-mail, containing at least the following information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li class="list-decimal ml-5">name, surname, address and other identification data of the person;
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
        </li>
        <li class="list-decimal ml-5">description of your request;
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
        </li>
        <li class="list-decimal ml-5">preferred form of providing the requested information;
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
        </li>
        <li class="list-decimal ml-5">date of submission of the application and address for correspondence.
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <p>The deadline for considering the application is one month, starting from the date of the application.</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500">&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500"><strong>5. Rules for processing personal data from www.fairykids.bg:</strong></p>
    <p>This privacy statement describes the ways in which www.fairykids.bg collects, holds and uses information about individuals who visit this website. By using this website, you consent to the collection and use of information as set forth in this Privacy Policy.</p>
    <p>You also acknowledge that www.fairykids.bg may periodically, at its discretion and without notice, amend, supplement or revoke or otherwise update this privacy policy.</p>
    <p>However, we will at all times handle your personal information in accordance with the Privacy Policy in effect at the time of collection.</p>
    <p>We intend to post changes to our privacy policy on this page so that you are fully informed about the types of information we collect, how we use that information, and under what circumstances it may be disclosed.</p>
    <p>Our Privacy Policy is posted on our home page and is available on any page where personal data is requested. Where data is collected, additional explanations may be given, if applicable, about the purposes for which the data will be used</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500">&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500"><strong>6. Privacy Policy</strong></p>
    <p>As used in this Privacy Policy, the term "personal data" refers to information, such as your name, date of birth, email, mailing address or telephone number, that can be used to identify you.</p>
    <p>We, as a licensed data controller, process personal data only as set out in this Privacy Policy.</p>
    <p>We reserve the right to carry out additional processing to the extent permitted or required by law, necessary to comply with relevant laws and regulations.</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500 text-3xl">&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500 text-3xl">&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500 text-3xl"><strong>The following sections explain how and when we will collect your personal data.</strong></p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500">&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500">&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500"><strong>1. Purpose of personal data</strong></p>
    <p>Most of the services we offer do not require any form of registration. This allows you to visit our site without telling us who you are.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>However, some services may require you to provide us with your personal data. In such case, if you choose not to provide the personal data we request, you will not be able to access certain parts of the site, and we will not be able to respond to your inquiries.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>It is possible, if you explicitly indicate your consent to this, in the profile settings or during registration, that we collect and use your personal data to inform you about campaigns, games and/or promotions that we think may be of interest to You, or to communicate with you for another purpose that is apparent from the circumstances or about which we inform you when collecting personal data from you.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500"><strong>2. Protection of personal data</strong></p>
    <p>We will not sell, share or otherwise transfer your personal information to third parties except as provided in this Privacy Policy. Personal data may be transferred to third parties acting on our behalf for further processing in accordance with the purpose(s) for which it was originally collected, or to be lawfully processed in another way, such as delivery of services, evaluating the usefulness of this website, marketing, data management or technical support.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>These third parties have agreed with us to use personal information only for the agreed purpose and not to sell or disclose your personal information to third parties except as required by law, permitted by us or in accordance with in this Privacy Policy.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>It is also possible that the personal data collected from you will be transferred to a third party in the event that the commercial activity of this site or part thereof and the customer data associated with it is subject to sale, assignment or transfer, in which case we will we require the buyer, assignee or transferee to treat personal data in accordance with this Privacy Policy. In addition, personal data may be disclosed to a third party if we are required to do so by applicable law, court or governmental act, and in the event that disclosure of personal data is necessary in connection with criminal or other legal proceedings investigation or proceedings in the country or abroad, after an act expressly duly submitted to the relevant court or Prosecutor.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500"><strong>3. Right of access, rectification and objection</strong></p>
    <p>Whenever we process personal data, we take reasonable steps to ensure that your personal data is accurate and up-to-date for the purposes for which it was collected. If the processing is not reasonably necessary for a legitimate business purpose as described in this policy or for our compliance with the law, we will give you the opportunity to object to the processing of your personal data.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>In the case of electronic direct marketing, we will offer you a way to opt-out of receiving marketing materials or a way to opt-out if required by law. At any time, you can request that we correct or delete your personal data from the database by doing so in writing to the address: BULGARIA, city of Plovdiv, p.k. 4023, g.k. Thrace, entrance A, fl. 5, apartment 15, company: "ALFA VISION INVEST" EOOD or to our e-mail: contact@fairykids.bg</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500"><strong>&nbsp;4. Cookies and Internet Tags</strong></p>
    <p>We may collect and process information about your visits to this website, such as the pages you visit, the website you came from, and some of the searches you perform.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>We use this information to improve the content of the site and for statistical information about the persons who use our site for internal purposes related to market research.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>In this process, we may install cookies that collect information about the user's domain name, your Internet service provider, your operating system, and the date and time of access.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>A "cookie" is a small piece of information sent to your browser and stored on your computer's hard drive. Cookies do not damage your computer. You can set your browser to notify you when you receive a "cookie", which will allow you to decide whether you want to accept it or not. However, we would like to inform you that if you do not accept cookies, you will not be able to use the full functionality of your browser software. We may also receive the services of third parties who assist us in collecting and processing the information described in this section.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>We may sometimes use Internet tags (also known as "action tags", "single-pixel GIFs", "clear GIFs", "invisible GIFs" and "1-by-1 GIFs") and cookies on this site, and implement them through a third party advertising partner or web analytics partner that is located and stores the relevant information (including your IP address) in another country.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>These tags/cookies are placed both in online advertisements that lead users to this site and on various pages on this site. We use this technology to measure the response behavior of visitors to our sites and the effectiveness of our advertising campaigns (including how many times a page is opened and what information is viewed), and to evaluate your use of this website.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>With the help of these tags/cookies, the third party partner or web analytics partner can collect data about visitors to our and other sites, prepare reports for us about website activity and provide other services related to website usage and internet. These partners may provide the collected information to other persons if there is such a legal requirement or if they engage other persons to process information on their behalf.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><strong>Google Analytics</strong></p>
    <p>"Google Analytics" is a service offered by the corporation Google Inc., through which detailed statistics are prepared about the traffic of a given website and the sources of traffic, and the levels of conversion of users into customers (conversion) and sales. Google Analytics uses cookies stored on your computer to analyze how users use our website.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>The information generated by the cookie about your use of our website, including your IP address, will be anonymized by using the relevant settings (the "_anonymizelp()" function or an equivalent function) and transmitted to Google servers.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Google will use the information created by the cookies on our behalf for the purpose of evaluating the use of our website, compiling reports on website activity and providing us with these reports for analysis purposes.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>Google may transmit this information to third parties if there is a legal obligation or if a third party processes data on Google's behalf. Google will under no circumstances combine or associate your IP address with other data stored by Google.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p>By using our website, you consent to the processing of any personal data that Google will collect about you in the manner or for the purposes specified above.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p class="text-pelorous-500"><strong>5. Links to other sites</strong></p>
    <p>This privacy policy applies only to this website and not to websites owned by third parties. We may post links to other websites that we think may be of interest to our visitors. We aim to ensure that these websites are of the highest standard. However, due to the nature of the Internet, we cannot guarantee the privacy standards of websites to which we link, or be responsible for the content of other sites other than this site, and this Privacy Policy is not intended to apply to any to be linked to a site that is not owned by www.fairykids.bg</p>
